The paper discusses the design of distributed algorithms for multiagent systems, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and multiagent systems (cs.MA). The focus is on cost-minimization problems, which can be considered as a type of optimization problem, placing it under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of linear programming, which is a common tool in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
